    <section id="id-600778556288">
      <title>Section 1: Language Focus</title>
      <para id="id3826005">Taking booking</para>
      <para id="id3826009">Here are some of the expressions the travel agent uses when taking the booking.</para>
      <para id="id3826018">Can I help you?</para>
      <para id="id3826022">I’ll check availability on the 14th of November.</para>
      <para id="id3826039">Do you want to confirm it?</para>
      <para id="id3826043">Can I take some details?</para>
      <para id="id3826048">I’ll just give you the booking reference number?</para>
      <para id="id3826054">Asking questions</para>
      <para id="id3826058">In formal situations it is more polite to ask questions indirectly, especially at the beginning of a conversation. For example, it can be better to use an indirect form such as Could you tell me when you were born? rather than When were you born?</para>
      <table id="id3826081" summary="">
